# Forms Guide

## Creating a Form

### 1. Templ component

```
// internal/web/handler/things/templates.templ
package things

import "{{.Module}}/internal/web/components/form"

templ CreateForm(errors map[string]string, csrfToken string) {
    <form method="POST" action="/things">
        @form.CSRFField(csrfToken)

        <div class="form-group">
            <label for="name">Name</label>
            <input type="text" id="name" name="name"
                hx-post="/things/validate/name"
                hx-trigger="blur"
                hx-target="#name-error"
                hx-swap="outerHTML"/>
            @form.FieldError("name", errors)
        </div>

        <div class="form-group">
            <label for="email">Email</label>
            <input type="email" id="email" name="email"
                hx-post="/things/validate/email"
                hx-trigger="blur"
                hx-target="#email-error"
                hx-swap="outerHTML"/>
            @form.FieldError("email", errors)
        </div>

        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Create</button>
    </form>
}
```

### 2. Handler

```go
// GET /things/new
func (h *Handler) NewPage(c echo.Context) error {
    token := c.Get("csrf").(string)
    return respond.HTML(c, http.StatusOK, CreateForm(nil, token))
}

// POST /things
func (h *Handler) Create(c echo.Context) error {
    name := c.FormValue("name")
    email := c.FormValue("email")

    errs := h.validate(name, email)
    if len(errs) > 0 {
        token := c.Get("csrf").(string)
        return respond.HTML(c, http.StatusUnprocessableEntity, CreateForm(errs, token))
    }

    // Save to database...

    middleware.SetFlash(c, "Created successfully!", middleware.FlashSuccess)
    return c.Redirect(http.StatusSeeOther, "/things")
}
```

### 3. Inline validation endpoint

```go
// POST /things/validate/name
func (h *Handler) ValidateName(c echo.Context) error {
    msg := validate.Required(c.FormValue("name"))
    return respond.HTML(c, http.StatusOK, form.FieldErrorOOB("name", msg))
}
```

## CSRF Token

The CSRF middleware stores the token in `c.Get("csrf")`. Use
`form.CSRFField(token)` in your templ components and the `htmx:configRequest`
listener in `layout.templ` automatically attaches it to HTMX requests via the
`X-CSRF-Token` header.

## Flash Messages

```go
middleware.SetFlash(c, "Saved!", middleware.FlashSuccess)
return c.Redirect(http.StatusSeeOther, "/things")
```

Read in templates: `components.GetFlash(c)` returns `*middleware.FlashMessage`
with `.Message` and `.Type` fields.
